The implications of the circular spinning nature, as we discussed in the last section are far reaching. The first and the most important, and the first in the order is to discuss   the garbage collection. As we said in the hypothesis, the `Bramha` - the overarching system implments a superior garbage collection process. Why superior ?

There is nothing in the nature that is not fully biodegradable. In other words nature doesn't make plastics :-) . Even the poop is useful. Wonder where your organic food comes from ? The question is why is everything so easily breakable when the reality seems so unbreakable ? Where do things go ? Is there a circle that is invisible to us ? 

The answer is simple an subtle. The circle of life ..
